<br>
Chapter 1 The Trueshot Bow Quest<br>
<br>
Hearing of the Trueshot Bow quest I set out to compleat it. I knew it was for Paladins, but who cares it was the adventure I was seeking. I set out for Steamfont for the gears I would need. I explored every valley from Kelethin to Lesser Faydark. I discovered a Pixie tower, I found dangerous shadow men, and many more discoveries there in the deep forest.<br>
<br>
I also found a perfect place to worship Mother Tunare, a cool peaceful green glade. It seemed as if she was there herself. Clearing my mind I could Meditate here better than I had ever done. <br>
<br>
I made my way to Steamfont after this with renewed strength. I was soon at the windmill hunting cleaner spiders. I only found one of the gears after what seemed like hours of battle. I being more interested in seeing what was there traveled to Akanon. It was loud and noisy TICK TICK TICK, I quickly left. <br>
<br>
Back out in the open air I traveled the land seeing strange and new beast, Minotaur, Kobolts and more. After my adventures here and collecting the needed gears I returned to Kelethin and put my treasures in the bank. <br>
<br>
I needed to go to Sister Island for Kiola Nuts. I set out for Butcher Block and Kalidim. I would have to spend many days traveling, exploring, seeking out adventure before I came upon this Dwarven City. Then on to the docks to catch the boat that would take me to my destination.<br>
<br>
It was here that I met a young man of the same season as I. He was very impetuous asking me to marry him.. ?? What I said surprised. &quot;I am going to be one of the Famous, The Rich and The Powerful of Norath&quot; he bragged. &quot;You may be my queen&quot;<br>
<br>
I stood back and asked &quot;What?? Sir marriage is for lovers and I am no more than a child. I have been called into the service of Mother Tunare just seven seasons ago now. I have only the love for adventure and service of my Mother Tunare. I hope to one day be a priestess&quot; <br>
<br>
There I had said it &quot;I hoped one day to be a priestess in the service of Mother Tunare?&quot; The words seeking the truth in my heart.. Marriage was not meant for me?&quot; To be a priestess one must be pure of heart, mind, spirit and body. The words surprised even me, was this my destiny? Was this why she had called me so young? Was this what the Heartwood Master had seen? <br>
<br>
I arrived at the docks eagerly awaiting the boat that was to take me to Sister Island and beyond. <br>
<br>
I sat thinking of what had been revealed to me earlier.. &quot;A Priestess?&quot; This would take some time to sort out? Could I ever be happy in just one place. Would I learn to have the faith that was required, the strength, the calm quietness of spirit, mind and soul. Mother Tunare only knew this, look at where she had lead me now? I resigned myself to the fact that only time would tell.<br>
<br>
My thoughts were interrupted by someone shouting &quot;Boat&quot;, I looked up to see a ship docking. Quickly I boarded this vessel and bid Faydwer &quot;Good bye&quot;. <br>
<br>
The Ocean of Tears was vast, the islands we passed contained creatures the likes I had never imagined It seemed to take forever as the day turned into night. I became restless and felt trapped by the confinement of the ship. Just when I could stand it no more the boat docked. at a small Island. I asked &quot;Is this Sister Island&quot;, back came the reply &quot;Yes&quot;.<br>
<br>
Not thinking there might be dangers on this Island I stepped off of the boat. Made it to the end of the dock before I realized there were Pirates here. I quickly moved to the small grouping of huts hoping to find safety there. Here was the reason for the name Sister Island. Here were the women who committed their lives to Mother Tunare. Purity was their symbol, as they wore belts of that name. <br>
<br>
I knowing that I might be lead into the same service asked all I could of them, they remained aloof from the arriving travelers. Strong and fierce they stood watch over the Island and themselves bound together by their beliefs and worship of Mother Tunare yet alone. Again I question my ability to ever become one of them knowing my heart for adventure. <br>
<br>
I purchased a sack full of Koila Nuts to take back to Kaladim to be made into Trumpy Tonics. I then waited at the dock for the next boat to arrive to take me on to Freeport for the last of the needed items to compleat the Trueshot quest. <br>
<br>
The boat came, I boarded her and soon were on our way to Freeport. I couldn't hide it my heart was full of excitement and joy. I sang songs and joked the whole way there I questioned everyone about Freeport and beyond. I'm afraid I was a bit annoying to my fellow travelers, they were a trapped audience on the boat with me. I would bound up and down the decks dancing and laughing like the child I was. By the end of the journey I'm sure they all felt the boat was much to small.<br>
<br>
Freeport came into view beautiful and shining in the days sun. I stood staring eager to get off to explore and adventure. In my innocence I wandered the streets looking in this shop that tavern. So young and wide eyed I took in everything.. <br>
<br>
Then danger! I passed a group of people killing the guards?? My heart pounded I could do nothing to help the guard nor did I understand why people would be so evil as to kill someone who was charged with the protection of the citizens here. I quickly hurried passed asking no questions keeping to myself, hoping no one would stop me or try to fight me. I hung my head in shame for my cowards. <br>
<br>
I finally made it to the bank where I deposited my sacks of Kiola Nuts. Then to purchase food and water, I entered a shop and asked if anyone had seen or knew where I could find Jyle Windshots. This was my question for many an hour. He had the needed Trent wood that I needed to take back to Maesyn Trueshot. I was given the the Rooster roost as his home and could find him there. Little did I know that this was an imposter. He asked for some items that made no sense to me. <br>
<br>
I gated home through the aid of my druid spell to fold time and space. I again asked about the quest, No this was not the right man I was told so of on the adventure again. But this time I stopped at Kalidim to get the necessary Trumpy tonic made and exchanged that for the Dwarven Wire. I repeated my boat trip and found myself at the dock in Freeport again. I quickly searched each and every building again asking where might I find this Jyle Windshots. I finally was told the Hogcallers Inn. There he was and I soon had my prize in hand. Once again gating back to Kelethin I gave the items to Maesyn Trueshot he gave me experience some money and a Trent Staff. <br>
<br>
Chapter 2 A New Land Antontica<br>
<br>
The Quest over, I searched for adventure more close to home. I was now strong enough to do some real damage at Orc Hill and even attempted to go into Crushbone several times to group. But it was all to familar same old stuff. Kill the Orcs. <br>
<br>
It grew wearisome after a while and as you now know I'm not one to stay in one place for long. Off I ventured roaming the land exploring all I could talking with anyone who had an adventure to tell or information to share. <br>
<br>
Soon I was back in Freeport and the area around it. I had nothing else to do but explore and time on my hands to see this world that Mother Tunare had made for me.<br>
<br>
This time out to the Desert of Ro where I met a fellow druid. The first time out she and I met Dorn B Dying and died quickly. I had the impression that he guard would save me but soon learned he was of little use against that Cutthroat.. <br>
<br>
So I learned the subtle art of run like hell from the Mad men, Zombies and Mummies as these creatures would surprise attack. I would be fighting an Orc Raider, snake, puma, or jackal. Just in the mist of battle they would appear and take your life if you didn't react fast enough. Many of times I learned this lesson and many more times did someone come to my aid. We would usually end up laughing about the mishap in the end. I met some very honorable men and women out on the sands.<br>
<br>
Time and again Mother Tunare Blessed me with guardian spirits. Many of whom I will never know their names and some like Minibfang who passed on to me an item of clothing or a weapon. I will never forget their kindnesses to me when I was so young and inexperienced. I learned to pass on to those younger and less experienced as I the same kindnesses shown me. In honor of all those that have in some way helped me.<br>
<br>
I soon learned that there was no place to train with a Druid Master close by. That there were to many dangers involved in going to Rivervale. It was Back to Kelithin, I didn't realize how much I missed being in the trees with the cool sweet grass. At the Dock I met a young druid man who needed a guide to Kelethin. Yaso was of the 7th level and also needed training so we joined together as traveling compainons.Once back home he bought spells and received training as did I. <br>
<br>
Now a 9th Leaf I was ready for even more adventure so Gated back to Freeport to continue my adventure on the Deserts Of Ro. I was now able to join groups to kill the Cutthroat thieves that had camps here. But soon found out that I quickly ran out of mana. I started asking around about how to increase this basic need. Soon I found out of the Skull of Jentra', found only on the planes of Karanas and beyond. I found out that the journey would be filled with many dangers, I had a better chance of dying that making it. <br>
<br>
I soon was preparing myself for the journey foolhardy as it seemed I needed that Skull and the adventure was calling me. &quot;Mother Tunare&quot; I prayed &quot;see fit to guild me in this to complete this task to better serve you.&quot; <br>
<br>
Chapter 3 Farvak<br>
<br>
At last I thought I am ready for the journey, I packed rations and water for the travel. Across the forested valley that was East and West Commons to the pass through Kithicor Wood. I paused and then entered into that dark place. Thinking to myself I was safe because it was day time. I had just sat to memorize camouflage when he came up to me. <br>
<br>
&quot;Hello there. My but you are a lovely little thing&quot;. I felt my face flush and turned my attention to the owner of that very seductive voice. Shyly I said &quot;Thank you. May you have safe and good journeys.&quot; A smile passed his face as he asked &quot;Where are you headed?&quot; I trustingly said to The planes of Karana to obtain a &quot;Skull of Jentra&quot;. He the asked if he could join me on my journey through this forest and make sure I made it safely to High Hold Pass.<br>
<br>
I was more than happy to have an experienced companion to help me through, from what I had heard was one of the most dangerous legs of my journey. We started up the long trail to High hold when he said &quot;Come over here I sense danger nearby&quot;. I quickly and trustingly followed him. Deep into the side of the wood away from the safety of the path.<br>
<br>
We finally stopped at a ruined building. He smilingly said here we would stay till it is safe, I innocently obeyed. We had time for conversation. He asked me many questions simple ones like where I was from, where was my family, who was my God. I answered unguarded and truthfully with an open heart. Then he became personal &quot;Had I ever been in love, had I ever know a lover&quot;<br>
.<br>
I blushed and replied &quot;No. I haven't the time for such things. My service to Mother Tunare has just begun&quot;. He laughed his eyes gleaming strangely. &quot; It is late and we cannot travel these woods at night&quot; he said. &quot;I will keep watch, you need to sleep&quot;<br>
<br>
I trusted him so much, with such blind innocence. I still cringe at my own ignorance. I awoke alone. The woods were always so Dark and not knowing my way or how to get out, where was he?. What had happened to him, I worried. Blood was all around was it his?? I sat there shivering my mind spinning with thoughts of a battle where he was torn to shreds so close begging for help and here I lay sleeping. It seemed as though hours passed and I could not find the courage to move from the spot. <br>
<br>
That was when I hear him call my name &quot;Katreena, your still here girl&quot; Laughingly he came and joined me. I was so relived that he was alive. &quot;What happened to you why is the camp full of blood?&quot; I eagerly questioned. &quot;Oh, that. Give it not a second thought. I am safe and now so are you&quot; His eyes gleamed strangely again. &quot;Here I have some meat to cook we will eat and then head off&quot;. <br>
<br>
It was now that I sensed that something terrible was about to happen or had happened and that I was the cause of it. He was unpacking his back pack when I saw my mothers head roll out. He was watching my face delighted by the terror that was twisting it into screams. &quot;She was all to easy to kill you know&quot; he said smirking. I turned to run and he grabbed my hair and spun me around to look at him. &quot;No I'm not done with you yet, little one.&quot; It was now that I understood his gleaming eyes, all to late it all became so very clear to me. Yelling at him &quot;Why, What did I do, What did they do to deserve this&quot; He replied as he was holding me down and wrapping my hands and feet in cords. &quot;Nothing that's just it&quot; confused and angry I could only stare in shock at his face. <br>
<br>
&quot;Come I have more to show you,&quot; he kept emptying those bags, forcing me to look at each piece as he brought it out. &quot;Your brother was a tough one, here is his heart, he held it out and whispered in my ear. The heart of a young warrior I believe you told me last night&quot;<br>
&quot;Your father on the other hand to easily killed, he was to old for the battle. Here are his eyes, a gift for you, love, so you will always know he is watching you.&quot; Your lovely sister delicious till the end. I do regret having to take her life so soon. I would have liked to taken her to my bed a few more times. But it is you that I want now more than ever. Your fall from innocence, to see your loss of faith and the hate you will allow to build up for Your Mother Tunare. It will consume you and you will serve me well&quot;. <br>
<br>
He commanded the evil things that were close, to come hold me there. I could only watch in terror. He just smiled and slowly undressed me keeping his eyes on mine all the while. &quot;I want to see the loss of innocence, do not turn from me. I will be gentle with you&quot;. He laughed evilly grinning now, his true nature poring from every inch. He coaxed &quot;Yes that is it, you know that all is hopeless now. Your just beginning to understand, humm how wonderful your fall is. No one to care, no one to know It was you who came willingly to my side, girl. You wanted me, maybe not this way but you want me even now your body gives you away. See how you tremble with excitement.&quot; <br>
<br>
Tears ran down my cheeks, terror filled my mind and the grief that was in my heart left me with the longing to die. I pleaded &quot;Kill me now. Have some mercy please&quot;. I screamed at the evil to rip my heart from my body. I begged Mother Tunare to release me from this world. None of that happened. &quot;Was this my punishment from Mother Tunare for being so disobedient, for wandering off so many times, for in my ignorance of youth when I had killed her wolves&quot;.<br>
<br>
He took me time and again. Each time more violent and savage he took great pleasure in torturing me. He would allow me to escape and have the evil around drag me back till I ran no more. Conceding to the fact that he had and would do with me as he pleased.All the time he was enjoying the rise of anger and hate that I would direct towards him.<br>
<br>
Words so vile spoken to me with such distaste. &quot;Katreena, I have soiled myself with you. Your now my whore and you will do as I please, I own you. Your Mother Tunare is no where to help you. She has cast you aside like trash, given you to me&quot;. I vowed time and again no man would ever have me again this way ever if I lived hardening my heart to all. Now, no tears would fall from my eyes. I would weep no more for my loss in front of him. I would deify him at every turn. <br>
<br>
Yet when I was left alone I would cry silently &quot;Mother Tunare why have you done this, what purpose of yours does this suit&quot;. All hope gone I could care no more what my fate may be.<br>
<br>
**************************<br>
<br>
I awoke, aching in a small hut with a young warrior sitting near by. &quot;Ah, your waking up. I thought for sure you would die. You are a strong willed girl&quot; Bitterly I looked at him and demanded &quot;Where am I?&quot; He answered gently &quot;Your in a small village just outside the pass to High Hold&quot;.<br>
<br>
&quot;And what vile evil do you have planed for me.&quot; I asked angry that I wasn't dead. &quot;Whoa! and that is my thanks for saving you?&quot; he replied. &quot;1st off, no one here is going to do anything to you, rest assured milady My name is Bioa, I am a young ranger I hunt these woods they are my home. The evil that had you has been slain. Trust me you are quite safe here. Now rest and regain your strength I will watch over you&quot;. <br>
<br>
Those words only brought back panic and terror. I sat up and spat &quot;NO! I will leave now. No one will ever keep a vigilance over me&quot; but then the room became a blur and I felt myself falling back and into darkness. Time and again I would awaken to this ranger watching over me. <br>
<br>
I would try to get up and leave, not trusting anything he said. But, I found all quickly each time that I was too weak. He would ask questions and I would just sit and stare him down silently. He would pass food to me, I would only take it if and when he moved away. Days had passed and I was Strong enough to leave. But fear kept me inside, I would go to the door open it and stop looking out. He finally said &quot;Let me take you to High Hold and you can journey from there, Please milady&quot; I said only the few words spoken to him in all this time &quot;And what do you want in return for this favor?&quot; He looked hurt but said &quot;Nothing, Lady, to see you on your way&quot;. I accepted that with doubts as he took the lead through the forest I kept him far enough away I could escape, but in view. <br>
<br>
We reached High Hold Pass and parted. &quot;Speedy journeys to you Lady and May Mother Tunare keep you safe&quot;. I angrily looked back and yet managed a &quot;Thank you for your help&quot;. I turned on my heals and never looked back again never wanting to be near Kithicor again.<br>
<br>
<br>
Chapter 4 On to Karanas<br>
<br>
I used camouflage to sneak past the Orc guards at the entrance to High Hold Pass from Kithicor Forest. I put behind me my last few days and pressed onward as if nothing ever had happened. There was nothing left to do but leave it behind me. <br>
<br>
Determined to finish my own quest, to gain the Skull of Jentra for my own. I set my mind to the task of finding the path through High Hold Pass that would take me to the vast planes of Karanas. <br>
<br>
Asking around I finally found someone to lead me through to the correct path down to East Karanas. The 2 men moved quickly however and lost me in the maze of passages. Lucky for me the gnolls there didn't detect me and I was soon following a path down a great mountain into a valley below. I still don't know how I found the right path out I had spent many hours walking in circles when I stumbled upon it. <br>
<br>
It took the better part of a day to reach the bottom. Just as I had a Lion was charging up the hill I again used camouflage to conceal my presents. I looked around as could see that this was not a good place to be there where Griffawns flying around, Gorge hounds, Spiders that were even more fierce than those in the Oasis of Mar, then to add to all this were Cyclopes, and Evil Eyes. <br>
<br>
I quickly moved onward to a small village stopping there only to buy more water. As I came out a Lion Matriarch attacked me I yelled for help as I fought the best I could. Someone took pity on my plight and killed the beast, I thanked them and asked for directions to South Karanas. &quot;Over the Wooden Bridge, move quickly, and be careful&quot; came the reply.<br>
<br>
I followed directions and soon was on the other side faced with new dangers. Borer Beatles, more Lions Highland, Lions, and Griffenes.. Oh I almost stopped and turned around then and there, but my desire for the Skull was greater than my fear. I moved on under the spell of Camouflage to a small gypsy camp there, I didn't delay there it seemed to dangerous to stop. <br>
<br>
I moved Southward to find myself at a Wizard Spire and Stone bridge. It was here that I met fellow travelers and asked if any of them had a Skull of Jentra for sale. None did but told me that I must seek out Lake Rathe and Kill a gnome embalmer. <br>
<br>
I was off again moving south. I gave a wide berth to the skeletons there. Then the most amazing creature passed me a Centaur, half man half horse creature. How wonderful they were, I had only hear tales of such creatures in my youth, never believing they were true, yet here they were. <br>
<br>
Then the ground shook under me, startled and afraid I once again used the camouflage spell to hide with. A great grey mass moved slowly on the horizon as I moved closer I saw it was an Elephant, majestic moving slowly like a ship across the plain. I was in awe of this land it held so much to see and to explore. I vowed to come back when I had the experience to walk among such beast. <br>
<br>
I came across a group on a hill, I asked where I might find the path to Lake Rath.. &quot;Oh and why travel so far from home.&quot; they asked, &quot;Your much to inexperienced to be here&quot;. I stood proudly and said &quot;I have traveled very far to buy a skull of Jentra, I will not leave till I have one&quot;. &quot;Well then You may have need of this&quot; a woman said and gave me a Tunic of Spilt Paw&quot;. I quickly bowed and said &quot;May Mother Tunare bless your journeys and safe health to you all. Thank you Lady, so very much&quot;. <br>
<br>
Again on my way south I came to the Aviak City, where Huge flightless birds dwelled. It was night and I was more than a bit frightened by the battles that were taking place down under the towers of that city in the sky. I shouted out &quot;Anyone Have a Skull Of Jentra for sale&quot;. &quot;Aye&quot; came the reply. A young dark elf quickly found me, once seeing my youth he laughed and said &quot;Here I have one in one of these bags&quot;. He quickly passed it to me I started to pay him, he quickly refused saying your bravery should be rewarded young one, use this wisely and pass it on when you no longer need it. <br>
<br>
Tears now filled my eyes as the generosity of this man was so touching to my soul. I thanked him quite humbly kneeling before him, He simply chuckled and bid me farewell.<br>
<br>
Chapter 5 Lost Faith, Found Faith<br>
<br>
I then used the spell gate to quickly take me back to Freeport to safety. Then to sad memories, I remembered that now I was alone in this world. No one here or in Kelethin to congratulate me on my quest. No one to brush the hair from my face to tell me how foolish I had been. No one to know of the pain I had suffered at the hands of Farvak and defend my now ruined Honor. <br>
<br>
Dreams were now shattered and like dust set upon the winds. I couldn't be a priestess for my Mother Tunare, no more was I pure and chased. I didn't know what She had in store for me. All I knew was I was alone and vowed that I would stay alone until I died.<br>
<br>
I had returned to Kelethin to lay to rest my family. To say good bye to them. To thank them for all they had done for me, to grieve for my loss of all that I knew. To punish myself for leaving them alone for so long. For telling Farvak where they were this was my shame and the guilt consumed me. My doubts about Mother Tunare crept in, I was unworthy to be a servant of hers. <br>
<br>
I then visited the Heartwood Master, I begged him for guidance. He just looked into my eyes and said &quot;You must find your faith again and in your own way, child. I see your pain, but only time will heal you now&quot;. I said nothing to him of Farvak, that was to remain my secret shame forever.<br>
<br>
I went to my most secret spot in Lesser Faydark and Meditated there. But no answers came, no rest, no peace could I find. My heart ached and my head was too full of memories an grief.<br>
<br>
I found myself back at Crushbone fighting Orc's, hoping that just doing something, anything, would ease the pain of my now broken heart and dreams. <br>
<br>
I met many new fighters, made pleasant talk, joined many a fine group all in an effort to eradicate the strong hold called Crushbone. My skills improved every day as the rage that was inside took it's toll on the Orcs. I reached my 10th Leaf quickly.<br>
<br>
One day a ranger of the 12th Leaf asked if I would like to go to the Mino Caves that there was better loot and experience to be had. Ready for a new adventure I followed him. Once there the mighty Minotaur Slavers became the focus of my anger. The Harpies too felt the pain that my staff could give and the power from the spells I cast. But again their deaths gave me no satisfaction from my own pain. This land Faydwer held only pain now I felt I had to leave.<br>
<br>
I knew as long as I kept moving I had no time to think or remember all I had lost. Back to Antonica again, to get lost in Freeport, I could become nothing more than just another face in the crowd. My family gone, my dreams gone, my faith gone, who was I, what was I to do with my life. Empty was what I felt, empty and alone.<br>
<br>
I boarded the ship at Butcher Block once again. The trip had become all to familar. I sat back wishing for the days of excitement, adventure, innocents and hope. But the world was now tainted, I was now suspicious and bitter. When we reached Freeport I moved quickly to get away from all the people, all the happiness, the excited travelers new to this land, the reunited families and lovers. <br>
<br>
Running, I was heading for the Desert where my eyes had become as dry as the sands there, my soul as parched as the bones, my future as empty and dead as the land. I joined group after group hunting and killing, but never staying in one place for more than a day. <br>
<br>
I would, if it became necessary to have grass under my feet, run through the Ro Tunnel to the Commonlands. It was on just such an occasion that I met a Druidess, Oceanwolf, who brought to my attention that I was killing wolves and bears. I said &quot;So,what? They are good experience and I need the money&quot;. She spoke softly &quot;The Master will not be pleased&quot;. She quickly pulled out her purse and said &quot;You may have all I have. Please do not dishonor Mother Tunare, your vows to her or your brothers and sisters this way&quot;. The tears in her eyes the way she spoke, it touched a spark in my dead heart.<br>
<br>
Shocked I looked at her and said &quot;No! Put your monies away. I have need to hear your words. Please come speak to me of Mother Tunare and help me to find my way back to Her favor. Help me find my faith&quot; I spent many hours with Oceanwolf as she spoke I found I was hungry for her words, her wisdom, her faith. It was she who taught me that I had given evil the power and in doing so had become that evil. The words stung like a slap in the face. I found more confusion in them than truth, but watched my own thoughts become clear again. <br>
<br>
It soon was time for Oceanwolf to go, but I promised her I would never ever kill another wolf or bear again. That I would seek out the truths she had given me, to search for the path that leads to the Light. Once again I could walk in the favor of Mother Tunare. I offered up prayer and praise to Her and found that it was She who had been beside me all the time. That I was the one to turn my back on Her, all I had to do was turn around to find Her.<br>
<br>
Chapter 6 The message<br>
<br>
I spent the next few seasons fighting the Orc's in East Commons, helping those less experienced than I. Passing on the truth of the Light that Mother Tunare had shown me. Then destroying the evil that inhabited the ruined Druid Rings there, zombies, lesser mummies and ghouls. When I had become proficient at this I went back to the North Desert Of Ro to clear out the ruined Druid Rings there. <br>
<br>
Taking the lives of the poor lost souls of the Mad Men, even when you tried to talk with them to help them gain their sanity they would attack. Only thing left to do was to kill them and pray. <br>
<br>
Back to West Commons where my heart broke over the many bodies of the Great Kodiak that where being slaughtered along with the Black Bears and my blessed brother Wolf. <br>
<br>
Just when I could stand it no more I discovered an evil strong hold. Befallen, the undead had taken over this place and their kind found sanctuary here. I was now close to my 14th Leaf, I saw this as a chance to prove to Mother Tunare my Faith in Her. I crushed the skeletons without stopping again and again clearing the first floor with ease..<br>
<br>
Then I discovered and confronted the Dark Elf Shadow Knight there in a small bedroom. My rage and hate took control I attacked without mercy the Hate filling my very being. When the battle was done I stepped back to see the slaughter and was sickened and frightened by my own actions. Not only had I killed him but there wasn't a piece of him big enough to recognize as life, I was soaked in blood. One eye across the room looked at me as if accusing me of becoming that evil thing. <br>
<br>
I ran in terror and shame, I ran to the lake and washed my body my clothing and everything I had. Then washed them again seeing blood where there was none. I scrubbed till I was raw. Then sat and cried, when there was no more tears I gathered my things and made camp.. Sleep was restless and I was exhausted, what had I done. I had lost control, there was evil inside me it would take over and Farvak would win. I had need of meditative prayer. I would have to find my center and cleanse my soul of this hate that had found a harbor there. <br>
<br>
At daybreak I set off for Rivervale, I was in need of a master to help guide me into my center, my soul. &quot;Oh&quot; I thought &quot;I wish Oceanwolf were here she would know exactly what to do and say to comfort me&quot;. I entered Kithicor Woods, the memories flooding me, I was shaking from fear.<br>
<br>
It was here that I again met Bioa. He and a few hunters had been killing the evil beings that had taken refuge here. He was wounded,and badly. I quickly bandaged him and then used my druid powers to heal him the rest of the way. Then moved to each member in his party. I asked if he was okay &quot;Yes, thanks to you Katreena. Why does that name sound familar?&quot; he asked <br>
<br>
&quot;Ah, you don't remember helping me to High Hold Pass. You sat for days and watched over me. I'm afraid that I was not very gracious. I have not properly Thanked You kind sir&quot; I replied.<br>
<br>
&quot;Oh yes, now your face looks familar. Consider me Thanked. How are you Lady&quot; He questioned. &quot;Fine, I have need of your help to reach Rivervale, Please if you would sir&quot; He quickly jumped to his feet, gave me a smile and said &quot;Gladly Milady, I am at your service&quot;. I shyly smiled and gave him thanks. We exchanged pleasantries as we made our way to Rivervale. I gave him what Druid Buffs I had and bid him good bye. <br>
<br>
Once there I went to the Druid Guild, spoke with the master Druid there. He again looked into my eyes and said &quot;Yes, Yes, I do see the need here you are troubled in your soul. Take this potion and go into Misty Thicket. Look for Mother Tunare in your heart. Drink this as you begin to Meditate. You will go on a soul journey. Now go&quot; I thanked him and left. <br>
<br>
I found Myself in dark forest of Misty Thicket, searching for just the spot that would help me to connect my soul to Mother Tunare's. Finally, tired, I sat down to rest before continuing. It was here that I felt Her call I quickly prepared myself. Giving Praise and thanks for all that she had blessed me with. I then drank the bitter potion. Only to find my head swimming in blackness a few minuets later. I tried to focus on my hands as best I could. They would come in and out of view and then gone. <br>
<br>
I felt myself floating... She came as a Light and spoke not with words but yet I heard her. &quot;Evil has no power unless you give evil Power. If you hate a thing you will become that thing&quot;. I could only form thought &quot;How do I not Hate that evil man for what was done to me&quot;. &quot;Show it My Love, child. Show it the Light of Tunare&quot; came the answer. <br>
<br>
I knew not how long I had been in this state or what I was to do with the message that was given to me. I was no more at peace with the hate inside of me than before. But I knew to have faith in Mother Tunare. All would be revealed to me in time. But questions still stirred, Did she want me to find Farvak and love him?? What! That made no sense, but then what?<br>
<br>
I found my way back to Rivervale and to the Druid Guild. I rested and spoke with the Master Druid. He wouldn't let me speak of what had been given to me. &quot;The message was for only you, you must find out what it means&quot; he said. I then asked for training, purchased the new spells for the 14th Leaf. <br>
<br>
I was at the bank when a more experienced Druidess asked if I needed Bone Hoop Earrings. &quot;Oh yes&quot; I replied. She asked me to stand there just a second. Then placed two in my hand. I tried to pay her and she refused. &quot;You need them now&quot; she smiled. I thanked her and bowed.<br>
<br>
I was just about to leave to go back to Commons when I overheard tell of a ring given to deputies that held<br>
a charge of heal, my eyes widened. I found out what it was that must be done. Kill goblins and turn in Runneyeye Warbeads to the Marshal till I gained favor with him. <br>
<br>
How many? What goblins, where? I asked around till I had the information. With 4 empty back packs to fill, I bound myself with my new spell to the entrance to Rivervale. Then ran to Misty Thicket to the Cave Mouth that opened to Runneyeye. There on either side were Goblin camps. I rolled up my sleeves and went to work. I spent weeks here killing those simple minded green goblins.<br>
<br>
I walked downstairs again to the other Marshal and asked &quot;Am I one with the Wall?&quot; I had done this time and again after each group of Warbeads was turned in. I waited for the answer, it came, I now held the ring. I was thrilled and quickly took it to the Casters Guild to Hummbl. Gave her the ring reluctantly, hoping she would charge it with the Heal spell and give it back to me. Yes.<br>
<br>
I also now had need of a special skill at the Druid Guild, Dodge I was now of the 15th Leaf. My efforts here had proved well spent. I had had time to hone my skills with the new spells and now had a new fighting skill as well.<br>
<br>
Chapter 7 <br>
<br>
I had grown tired of the darkness that was Misty Thicket, the goblins offered no challenge for me now. I had tried to enter Runnyeye on several occasions, but found it confining and I became lost in the maze of tunnels. I chose not to venture there until I had a few more seasons on me.<br>
<br>
I thought once again of Karanas, how I wanted to explore those vast plains. I knew that I was still to inexperienced to be of any success there. Next best thing was back to the Deserts of Ro.. I missed the sunshine and open air, the desert would surely give me my fill of both.<br>
<br>
I sat at the cave mouth to Kithicor Forest waiting for daybreak, when the evil that was there would take refuge in their dark holes. The passage through there would be fairly safe if one did not delay or stray from the path.<br>
<br>
There were a few others gathered here fighting the evil, vile things that had a stronghold here. I watched and would heal if I saw the need, inside cheering each victory won. It did my heart good to see that evil had to pay a price for it's existence. Soon it was time to get moving, I bid farewell to those at the cave and ran quickly towards West Commons. <br>
<br>
Upon reaching West Commons,I was drawn to the sounds of battle, Orc's grunting out death cries as two Men fought with them. I stopped and offered assistance, they offered to share the camp with me. We didn't group but instead I healed them and they would come to my aid if I needed help. I would give them the Orc belts that I came across for their share of my loot. We spent the day this way. They mentioned that I should go fight in the Oasis of Mar where the Orc's had a temple. I asked directions and made plans to head there the next day.<br>
<br>
I had stopped at the Inn close to the Toll both to East Commons where I was going to replenish my food and water when I was attacked from behind? What was this? I spun around and looked into a dark elf's face as he smiled evilly at me. I was puzzled and then all was black. Mother Tunare touched me and I awoke at Rivervale. I quickly gathered my thoughts, sat and remembered spells for the quick journey through Kithicor and beyond. It was no use to try and leave now as it was the middle of the night, I again would have to wait till morning. <br>
<br>
I awoke several times reaching for this item or that only to remember that my body lay in the Inn in West Commons. This was unnerving. I would cast camouflage on me just so not to be seen by passers by. As soon as it was morning I quickly ran the distance through Kithicor and to the Inn. <br>
<br>
I spotted my body, dragged it to the Toll Booth and the Guards there. I then collected my things. Who had killed me?? I thought one had to accept a duel to be killed by another. It was then that I heard the names Gix and Dragoon from a group close by. <br>
<br>
Dragoon took to the the area by the lake and Gix by the zone. They being of the Dark races roamed and ruled this area, killing any unsuspecting traveler unwary enough to pass through. I grew angry at the thought that I had been taken so easily, but thought better of challenging them as I had been killed so easily. One day I would have my vengeance until then I would bide my time.<br>
<br>
I headed onward to the Northern Desert of Ro when I heard tell of a Mummy that carried a magical rod. I again thought that this item would be a nice addition to my weapons. I heard tell that he was rarely ever seen but if he was it was by the Southern most Cutthroat Derv Camp by the wall. I would take down the Derv's there solo now and with very little trouble. <br>
<br>
However, after a week or so of not seeing this Mummy I became bored and moved on to the Oasis of Mar, to the ocean and then south to the docks. There I joined many a group by what was called the Orc Highway. It was the Sand Giants and the Specters that were ominous the rest was more of the same. At last I reached Level 17 here after many weeks of traveling between the Orc Highway and the Cutthroat Derv Camps. <br>
<br>
Time to visit Rivervale for new spells and training in the ways of the Druid. It was after I did this that I decided to try my skills at Tailoring. I purchased a large sewing kit and patterns, however I being a Druid and had vowed never to kill a wolf or bear. This would make this skill even harder to acquire. Spider webs would be my means of attaining most of my skills, I would however collect the pelts of bears and wolves from their dead bodies as a way to prevent waste and to honor their deaths.<br>
<br>
Chapter 8<br>
<br>
I had seen and heard tell of spiders in East Karanas that produced up to 4 webs per spider. Eager to start my training I was now headed there.<br>
<br>
On through High Hold Pass then down the long steep winding trail that lead to the valley and planes of East Karana.  I kept a sharp eye out once in the valley for the Cyclops brothers that roamed this land as well as the Evil Eyes. <br>
<br>
 My skin crawled with the thought of meeting any of these alone.  The Cyclops could kill you with one blow and the Evil eyes could cast spells that could make you blind and defenceless to fight them then there was the small mater of their pets.  Chances of me surviving at my leaf where slim I could always run for the bridge to North Karanas but that would put many of innocents in danger. No best to hide and avoid these beings for now. Ah, but one day I would challenge the evil ones and win.<br>
<br>
For now the spiders and lions would prove to be enough of a challenge for me. That and my lessons in tailoring, while I sat and regained mana, would keep me busy for now.  <br>
<br>
I stood on the vast plane eyeing the oncoming spider. lifting my staff to do battle.  I had become very good at what others had called Kiting the massive arachnids.  I cast snare slowing them down then between running and casting I could do enough damage that it took only a few blows to finish them off.   The problem was to stay out of reach of those poisonous fangs.  You may win the battle only to die afterwards from the poison they injected into your body, slow and painful was this death.<br>
<br>
Then there were the Matriarch lions.  Their muscular bodies and claws could kill the unwary quickly.  I learned to stay away from them when my health and mana where low. But when I was at full health and mana I could take them, they provided the pelts to increase my tailoring skills so that I was now able to sew patchwork armor. <br>
<br>
